snippet: Ahmad Tomeh ran unopposed and was said to be a consensus candidate accepted by a secular-leaning coalition within the Syrian National Council.
abstract: Syrian National Council, main Syrian opposition coalition, elects longtime dissident Ahmad Tomeh as provisional prime minister.
